         <blockquote>
         I can understand that it takes a certain character or RPer to bring life to a game. The feeling of a certain hero player or group of players ready to chop your head off might make that person very afraid since they know they will soon be dead. This makes a good REAL RP feeling and IS the great foundation of player verses player environment. So there is a certain time building up courage to fight the super hero like you brought out very clear even for the peon. As you can see, I am not blind to that.<P> I am blind to the KAAOS dream of being able to bring pure evil to a game. All a person has to do if they are being harassed or slaughtered over and over again is to stop playing with the person bringing evil actions to him/her and to begin playing in a more newbie town or play another character in a different faction or clan. That way the roles are reversed and the hunted become the hunter. <P>So in short I do agree Role Play brings a great deal of excitement before a fight, during a fight, and after a fight. Most times I would wait a few seconds getting pumped up like the old western movies before a gunfight duel. The Matrix would also be a good example along with Bruce Lee movies. <P>There has to be anticipation and preparation. A style along with dialogue as well to have a good pvp game.<P>Not any surprise you’re dead!
         </blockquote>
